class.rdfs:comment: Any biological, chemical, or biochemical thing. For example: a protein; a gene; a chemical; a synthetic chemical.
class.rdfs:label: BioChemEntity

schema:associatedDisease.rdfs:comment: Disease associated to this BioChemEntity. Such disease can be a MedicalCondition or a URL. If you want to add an evidence supporting the association, please use PropertyValue.
schema:associatedDisease.rdfs:label: associatedDisease

schema:bioChemInteraction.rdfs:comment: A BioChemEntity that is known to interact with this item.
schema:bioChemInteraction.rdfs:label: bioChemInteraction

schema:bioChemSimilarity.rdfs:comment: A similar BioChemEntity, e.g., obtained by fingerprint similarity algorithms.
schema:bioChemSimilarity.rdfs:label: bioChemSimilarity

schema:biologicalRole.rdfs:comment: A role played by the BioChemEntity within a biological context.
schema:biologicalRole.rdfs:label: biologicalRole

schema:funding.rdfs:comment: A [[Grant]] that directly or indirectly provide funding or sponsorship for this item. See also [[ownershipFundingInfo]].
schema:funding.rdfs:label: funding

schema:hasBioChemEntityPart.rdfs:comment: Indicates a BioChemEntity that (in some sense) has this BioChemEntity as a part.
schema:hasBioChemEntityPart.rdfs:label: hasBioChemEntityPart

schema:hasMolecularFunction.rdfs:comment: Molecular function performed by this BioChemEntity; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.
schema:hasMolecularFunction.rdfs:label: hasMolecularFunction

schema:hasRepresentation.rdfs:comment: A common representation such as a protein sequence or chemical structure for this entity. For images use schema.org/image.
schema:hasRepresentation.rdfs:label: hasRepresentation

schema:isEncodedByBioChemEntity.rdfs:comment: Another BioChemEntity encoding by this one.
schema:isEncodedByBioChemEntity.rdfs:label: isEncodedByBioChemEntity

schema:isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.rdfs:comment: Biological process this BioChemEntity is involved in; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.
schema:isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess.rdfs:label: isInvolvedInBiologicalProcess

schema:isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.rdfs:comment: Subcellular location where this BioChemEntity is located; please use PropertyValue if you want to include any evidence.
schema:isLocatedInSubcellularLocation.rdfs:label: isLocatedInSubcellularLocation

schema:isPartOfBioChemEntity.rdfs:comment: Indicates a BioChemEntity that is (in some sense) a part of this BioChemEntity.
schema:isPartOfBioChemEntity.rdfs:label: isPartOfBioChemEntity

schema:taxonomicRange.rdfs:comment: The taxonomic grouping of the organism that expresses, encodes, or in someway related to the BioChemEntity.
schema:taxonomicRange.rdfs:label: taxonomicRange
